verbs.description: unsceptre (third-person singular simple present unsceptres, present participle unsceptring, simple past and past participle unsceptred)

entries.meaning: To deprive of a sceptre; to deprive of the status of monarch or of authority.
examples: Synonyms: decrown, depose, descepter, dethrone, discrown, disenthrone, uncrown, unking, unthrone
